00:14:22,972 --> 00:14:25,936
The game meets us in this particular layer of our being.

250
00:14:26,056 --> 00:14:28,279
The game meets us in this case on our narrative mind.

251
00:14:28,499 --> 00:14:31,343
But to understand what makes a MOBA like this

252
00:14:31,424 --> 00:14:33,526
so entrancing, we need to go deeper

253
00:14:33,567 --> 00:14:34,348
than the narrative mind.

254
00:14:36,694 --> 00:14:45,502
And just as our identity, our sense of identity emerges as a trance from our habits of self-reflectivity

255
00:14:45,602 --> 00:14:50,927
in our narrative mind, so too does the narrative mind itself emerge from the emotional body.

256
00:14:51,328 --> 00:14:56,272
The mind labels emotions, numbing them in a symbolic container so that we're not crippled

257
00:14:56,312 --> 00:14:56,713
by fear.

258
00:14:57,193 --> 00:15:00,676
And the mind also helps us understand the causes and effects of our emotions

259
00:15:00,976 --> 00:15:05,239
so that we can move intelligently towards the sources of positive emotions

260
00:15:05,279 --> 00:15:07,140
and away from the sources of negative emotions.

261
00:15:08,481 --> 00:15:11,343
So the MOBA is not only meeting us in our narrative mind,

262
00:15:11,404 --> 00:15:14,066
it's also strongly meeting us in our emotional body.

263
00:15:14,106 --> 00:15:17,788
I think that flow trance I drew out is really an emotional body trance.

264
00:15:18,925 --> 00:15:22,366
And activating people in the narrative mind

265
00:15:22,726 --> 00:15:23,626
and in the emotional body,

266
00:15:24,026 --> 00:15:25,806
I think that's something games do really well.

