00:16:21,846 --> 00:16:25,268
But we're using, it's also a different kind of trance from a MOBA and we're going to go

283
00:16:25,288 --> 00:16:25,789
into how.

284
00:16:26,669 --> 00:16:29,811
So the words we're using here to describe these trances.

285
00:16:30,597 --> 00:16:32,539
These are kind of attention words.

286
00:16:32,919 --> 00:16:36,623
These are words describing a sort of deeper layer

287
00:16:36,643 --> 00:16:38,444
of our being than the words we're using

288
00:16:38,464 --> 00:16:40,086
to describe the trances in a MOBA,

289
00:16:40,126 --> 00:16:42,828
which are much more action-heavy, action-oriented.

290
00:16:42,969 --> 00:16:45,010
And this is a fantastically complex trance.

291
00:16:48,494 --> 00:16:52,197
So if the mindfulness trance is operating

292
00:16:52,237 --> 00:16:53,238
on the domain of attention,

293
00:16:53,258 --> 00:16:55,620
then what is it even is attention?

294
00:16:56,041 --> 00:16:56,861
Attention is...

295
00:16:59,702 --> 00:17:04,464
the highlighting and the feeding of certain aspects of our felt experience.

296
00:17:05,765 --> 00:17:09,506
So even thoughts, you know, the content of your thoughts is certainly something that

297
00:17:09,626 --> 00:17:14,088
occurs in our narrative mind, that we experience as narrative mind, but you can feel the feeling

298
00:17:14,248 --> 00:17:14,809
of your thoughts.

299
00:17:15,089 --> 00:17:19,951
And this is a sense just like heat is a sense, just like smell is a sense, just like the

300
00:17:19,991 --> 00:17:20,771
sound of my voice.

