00:19:18,908 --> 00:19:20,828
as being a little bit like a digital zen koan.

340
00:19:22,729 --> 00:19:25,950
So, where are mechanics meet, and stories,

341
00:19:26,250 --> 00:19:28,170
where are mechanics and stories meet the player

342
00:19:28,390 --> 00:19:30,711
in this massively complex trance we call the self?

343
00:19:32,223 --> 00:19:34,465
has a tremendous impact on the player's experience.

344
00:19:34,665 --> 00:19:38,429
But not only the player's experience, who they are.

345
00:19:39,930 --> 00:19:41,571
How our mechanics meet the player

346
00:19:42,512 --> 00:19:43,773
at any of these layers of self

347
00:19:44,214 --> 00:19:45,635
determines who the player is,

348
00:19:45,855 --> 00:19:47,317
who they are practicing being.

349
00:19:47,937 --> 00:19:49,619
And you can meet the player, for example,

350
00:19:49,639 --> 00:19:52,161
in the emotional body and have them practicing fear.

351
00:19:52,541 --> 00:19:54,003
Or you can meet them in the emotional body

352
00:19:54,043 --> 00:19:55,424
and have them practicing compassion.

353
00:19:56,236 --> 00:20:01,497
If you meet them in the emotional body in such a way that it modifies existing trances

354
00:20:02,617 --> 00:20:08,398
or habits in the other layers of their being, then you can effectively reprogram the narrative

355
00:20:08,438 --> 00:20:10,039
mind or the higher layers of being.

